<br>
1) EQ has a command, /note. This is a documented command, meant to be used by players. Furthermore, it is written to a file, 'notes.txt', meant to be read by the players. There is nothing illegal about that.<br>
<br>
2) This program manipulates that file, and perhaps the standard logfile, by reading and parsing it.<br>
<br>
3) This program does nothing else related to EQ. It does not tamper with it.<br>
<br>
Now, SOE is going to make you stop?<br>
<br>
Sorry, I won't deal with that. I've begun coding a replacement program if you are giving up.<br>
<br>
And as for your '.... and all you free speech people' comment on your main page:<br>
<br>
This is very important. If they don't want the notes.txt file and logfiles to be used, they should not be in the EQ program, and documented. If they allow us, the players, to read and use those files, they cannot disallow us to write programs to read them, either. Very simple. If they have an issue, take out the /note command and the logging functionality.<br>
